    "body": "@gerchicov-bp This should be possible using a library that parallelizes promise execution. [This one](https://www.npmjs.com/package/async-await-parallel) looks like it might work nicely for migrations. It would look something like this:\r\n```javascript\r\nconst parallel = require('async-await-parallel');\r\n\r\nmodule.exports = function (deployer) {\r\n  deployer.then(async () => {\r\n    return parallel(\r\n      deployer.deploy(MyContract1),\r\n      deployer.deploy(MyContract2)\r\n    )\r\n  })\r\n}\r\n```\r\n",
